Package org.pitest.mutationtest.engine.gregor

Interface MethodMutatorFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AODMutator, AORMutator.MathMutator1, AORMutator.MathMutator2, AORMutator.MathMutator3, AORMutator.MathMutator4, ArgumentPropagationMutator, BooleanFalseReturnValsMutator, BooleanTrueReturnValsMutator, ConditionalsBoundaryMutator, ConstructorCallMutator, EmptyObjectReturnValsMutator, IncrementsMutator, InlineConstantMutator, InvertNegsMutator, MathMutator, MemberVariableMutator, NakedReceiverMutator, NegateConditionalsMutator, NonVoidMethodCallMutator, NullMutateEverything, NullReturnValsMutator, PrimitiveReturnsMutator, RemoveConditionalMutator, RemoveIncrementsMutator, RemoveSwitchMutator, ReturnValsMutator, ReturnValuesMutator, RORMutator.RORMutator1, RORMutator.RORMutator2, RORMutator.RORMutator3, RORMutator.RORMutator4, RORMutator.RORMutator5, SwitchMutator, UnviableClassMutator, VoidMethodCallMutator

    public interface MethodMutatorFactory
    A MethodMutatorFactory is a factory creating method mutating method visitors. Those method visitors will serve two purposes: finding new mutation points (locations in byte code where mutations can be applied) and applying those mutations to the byte code.

    A MethodMutatorFactory will have a globally unique id and must provide a human readable name via the getName() method. This name will be used in the reports created to document and describe the mutation(s) applied.

    Author:
    Henry Coles
